name: r-spatialtools
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.0.4' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-spatialtools
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/SpatialTools_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/SpatialTools/SpatialTools_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 3828fba9296bf4159d771c938ff12c972b943d663ef862368c9b4ed1f5cfeb49

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rcpp
    - r-rcpparmadillo >=0.3.0
    - r-spbayes >=0.3.0
    - libblas
    - liblapack
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-rcpp
    - r-rcpparmadillo >=0.3.0
    - r-spbayes >=0.3.0

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('SpatialTools')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('SpatialTools')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=SpatialTools
  license: GPL-2.0-or-later
  summary: Tools for spatial data analysis.  Emphasis on kriging.  Provides functions for prediction
    and simulation.  Intended to be relatively straightforward, fast, and flexible.
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r

# Package: SpatialTools
# Type: Package
# Title: Tools for Spatial Data Analysis
# Version: 1.0.4
# Author: Joshua French <joshua.french@ucdenver.edu>
# Maintainer: Joshua French <joshua.french@ucdenver.edu>
# Depends: R (>= 3.0.2)
# Imports: spBayes (>= 0.3.0), Rcpp
# LinkingTo: Rcpp (>= 0.9.10), RcppArmadillo (>= 0.3.0)
# Description: Tools for spatial data analysis.  Emphasis on kriging.  Provides functions for prediction and simulation.  Intended to be relatively straightforward, fast, and flexible.
# License: GPL (>= 2)
# LazyLoad: yes
# NeedsCompilation: yes

# Repository: CRAN
